{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-piranga-roseogularis", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-piranga-roseogularis", "name": "Rose-throated tanager", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "taxonomy-genus-piranga", "name": "Piranga", "latinName": "Piranga", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Piranga（Piranga）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联9种鸟类，如Red-headed tanager、Red-hooded tanager、Rose-throated tanager等9种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 9, "x": -683.36, "y": 24.62, "z": -23.86}, {"id": "taxonomy-species-piranga-roseogularis", "name": "Rose-throated tanager", "latinName": "Piranga roseogularis", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Rose-throated tanager（Piranga roseogularis）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Rose-throated tanager。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": 255.01, "y": -81.71, "z": 119.77}, {"id": "bird-rose-throated-tanager-580af652", "name": "Rose-throated tanager", "englishName": "Rose-throated tanager", "latinName": "Piranga roseogularis", "type": "bird", "status": "LC", "summary": "The rose-throated tanager (Piranga roseogularis) is a medium-sized songbird in the family Cardinalidae, the cardinals or cardinal grosbeaks. Endemic to the Yucatán Peninsula in Central America, it is found in Belize, Guatemala, and Mexico. The male has greyish plumage with a deep rose throat and crown, while the female is similar but for a yellow crown and throat. Taxonomy and systematics American ornithologist Samuel Cabot III described the rose-throated tanager in 1846, having seen a pair in the Yucatán Peninsula and shooting the male. A 2019 genetic study using mitochondrial DNA showed that it was a basal (early offshoot) of a lineage that gave rise to the scarlet, hepatic, summer, western and flame-colored tanagers. The rose-throated tanager and the other species of genus Piranga were originally placed in the family Thraupidae, the \"true\" tanagers. Since approximately 2008 they have been placed in their current family, the Cardinalidae. The rose-throated tanager has three recognized subspecies, the nominate Piranga roseogularis roseogularis, P. r. tincta, and P. r. cozumelae. Description The rose-throated tanager is 16 cm (6.3 in) long and weighs 21 to 30 g (0.74 to 1.06 oz). The nominate male's crown and throat are deep rose and the rest of the body shades of gray. The folded wings and tail appear crimson. The female's crown and throat are yellow. The upper parts are yellowish olive and the underparts mostly pale gray to whitish. Its folded wings and tail are yellowish. P. r. tincta has the same color schemes as the nominate but is paler, and P. r. cozumelae is darker. Distribution and habitat The nominate rose-throated tanager is found in the northern, drier, part of Mexico's Yucatán Peninsula. P. r. tincta is found in the more humid southern part of the peninsula and in northern Guatemala and Belize. P. r. cozumelae is restricted to the islands of Mujeres and Cozumel off the east coast of the peninsula. The species primarily inhabits the edges of semi-humid and humid mature forest and the undergrowth of scrubby forest, although it sometimes is found in areas with scrub and only scattered trees. In elevation it ranges from sea level to 250 m (820 ft). Behavior Feeding The rose-throated tanager forages throughout most levels of the forest, in undergrowth, saplings, mid-level, and the canopy. In the last it often joins mixed-species foraging flocks. It has also been observed following army ant swarms. Details of its diet have not been published. Breeding No information on the rose-throated tanager's breeding phenology has been published. Vocalization The rose-throated tanager's song is \"a rich warbled 'whee chee cheer-el-chee cheer-el-cheu chee-el-chu...'\". Calls include a nasal \"rreh\" and a mewing \"myaaa\". Status The IUCN has assessed the rose-throated tanager as being of Least Concern. \"Although portions of the area within its range are subject to considerable human-caused environmental pressures, the species does not appear to be at any immediate risk.\" References External links Media related to Piranga roseogularis at Wikimedia Commons Data related to Piranga roseogularis at Wikispecies", "shortSummary": "The rose-throated tanager (Piranga roseogularis) is a medium-sized songbird in the family Cardinalidae, the cardinals or cardinal grosbeaks…", "locations": ["伯利兹", "危地马拉", "尤卡坦半岛"], "habitats": ["成熟森林"], "lat": 17.06666667, "lng": -88.7, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d1/Piranga_roseogularis_64951842.jpg/960px-Piranga_roseogularis_64951842.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-piranga", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-piranga-roseogularis", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-piranga", "species": "taxonomy-species-piranga-roseogularis"}, "expandable": true, "x": 255.01, "y": -81.71, "z": 132.02}], "links": [{"key": "bird-rose-throated-tanager-580af652__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-piranga-roseogularis", "source": "bird-rose-throated-tanager-580af652", "target": "taxonomy-species-piranga-roseogularis", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-piranga-roseogularis__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-piranga", "source": "taxonomy-species-piranga-roseogularis", "target": "taxonomy-genus-piranga", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：Rose-throated tanager 属于属 Piranga。"}]}
